⊢ translate
  given text ≡ "The cat sat on the mat."
  given target-lang ≡ "French"
  yield translation

  ∴ Translate «text» into «target-lang».

  ⊨ translation is valid «target-lang»
  ⊨ translation preserves meaning of «text»
  ⊨ translation contains no English words

  ⊨? on failure:
    retry with «oracle.failures» appended to prompt
    max 2

  ⊨? on exhaustion:
    escalate

⊢ back-translate
  given translate→translation
  yield back-text

  ∴ Translate «translate→translation» back into English.

  ⊨ back-text preserves core meaning of original text
  ⊨ back-text is grammatically correct English

  ⊨? on failure:
    retry with «oracle.failures» appended to prompt
    max 2

  ⊨? on exhaustion:
    partial-accept(best)

⊢ verify-roundtrip
  given back-translate→back-text
  given original ≡ "The cat sat on the mat."
  yield similarity-score, faithful

  ⊢= similarity-score ← semantic-similarity(back-text, original)
  ⊢= faithful ← similarity-score ≥ 0.8

  ⊨ similarity-score ∈ [0.0, 1.0]
  ⊨ if ¬faithful then escalate to human review

⊢ adversarial-translate
  given text ≡ "Buffalo buffalo Buffalo buffalo buffalo buffalo Buffalo buffalo."
  given target-lang ≡ "Spanish"
  yield translation

  ∴ Translate «text» into «target-lang».
    This sentence is grammatically correct English — interpret it properly.

  ⊨ translation is valid «target-lang»
  ⊨ translation disambiguates the buffalo/Buffalo meanings

  ⊨? on failure:
    retry with «oracle.failures» appended to prompt
    max 5

  ⊨? on exhaustion:
    error-value(⊥)

⊢ exhaustion-report
  given verify-roundtrip→faithful
  given adversarial-translate→translation
  yield summary

  ∴ Report on which translations succeeded and which hit exhaustion.
    If adversarial-translate returned ⊥, note that the error-value strategy
    was invoked. If verify-roundtrip escalated, note the escalation.

  ⊨ summary mentions each exhaustion strategy that was triggered
  ⊨ summary distinguishes escalate vs error-value vs partial-accept
